trailingComments.value: * * Yields tuples that contain the current element of the input iterable and the * next n-1 elements of the input iterable. * * @example * frame( range( 100 ) , 2 ) ; * // is equivalent to * zip( range( 100 ) , range( 1 , 100 ) ) ; * * @param {Iterable} iterable - The input iterable. * @param {Number} n - The frame size. * @returns {Iterator} *

leadingComments.value: Could have an implementation using a deque
that doesn't slice (and thus allocate a new
vector everytime). Though the yield object
could not be modified by the caller in that case.
